## Security Review — `app.js`

The application is a minimal Express.js server with two endpoints. While there are no *actively exploitable* bugs in 22 lines of hardcoded data, the code establishes patterns that are dangerous at scale and is missing every standard security layer. Here are the findings mapped to OWASP Top 10 (2021).

