app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourapp.com'], // explicit allowlist — never use '*' with credentials
  methods: ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'DELETE'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Content-Type', 'Authorization'],
  credentials: true,
}));
```

---

### 7. No Error Handling Middleware

Unhandled errors in Express will either crash the process or leak a stack trace to the client, exposing internal file paths, library versions, and logic.

**Risk:** OWASP A09 – Security Logging and Monitoring Failures; information disclosure.

**Fix:**

```js
// Must be the LAST middleware registered
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  // Log full error internally (to your logging service, never to the client)
  console.error({ err, url: req.url, method: req.method });

  // Return a generic message to the client
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'An unexpected error occurred' });
});
```

