| # | Issue | Detail |
|---|-------|--------|
| 7 | **Timestamp disclosure** | `/health` returns `new Date().toISOString()`. Minor, but server time can aid timing-based attacks and fingerprinting. |
| 8 | **No CORS policy** | No explicit CORS configuration means browsers rely on the default same-origin policy, which may be too permissive or too restrictive depending on deployment context. Explicitly configure CORS with an allowlist. |
